This is really fantastic. Well made, cool animations, my brain loves it. I have thought about the sequence numbers - its gets real difficult to manage. And changing a low number means all modules must be updated. It would be perfect if the modules were presented in a sequence bar down at the play pause controls. Then draging and dropping modules in that bar easily updates the sequence.
Its great! But I'm stuck on a puzzle and without a community or anymore ways to earn more hint points, I pretty much can't go on.

How does this have less than 5,000 downloads?  It's well made, only $1, it does not have advertising, and it does not require security permissions other than not causing the phone to sleep - great combination.  Save up your hint points since some of the later levels are quite difficult.  My feedback for the developers 1) The CPU usage could be lower.  Could you limit the frame rate? 2) Players should be given a reward for not using all of the modules. 3) The fastest animation speed could be faster. 4) Rather than requiring 4 balls to complete the level you could consider the level to be completed after the first ball goes in as soon as an iteration prior to the first ball is repeated. You could do this by keeping a HashSet of the state each iteration.  5) Add at least one level with unlimited modules so people can play with them.  This could evolve into a level editor.  6) Let people see your solution after they solve a level so they can compare.
